           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white">
                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Hope this little guide helps out.. I do an AA about every 1 1/2 to 2 hours with this little technique...<br /><br />Spell 1 root<br />Spell 2 Shackle (undead slow)<br />Spell 3 Thrall of bones<br />Spell 4 Deflux<br />Spell 5 DemiLich & Pet buff (yes higher lvl pet buff makes a difference)<br />Spell 6 E Bolt<br />Spell 7 Harmshield<br />Spell 8 Feign Death<br /><br />I've been doing undeads in between the 2 coterie buildings in Maidens eye.. Charm & buff a vampyre bat, cast tiny companion on it so you can tell it apart and park it up near the 2 rocks on the ledge near zone border just after the first coterie building (being amiable to coteries prolly helps me here) ..<br /><br />Pull any/all undeads in sight as long as they're somewhat seperated from the other mob as to get a single pull.. pull with shackles spirit (undead slow) sick pet on'm root and cast ebolt 1 ebolt should be plenty to kill other bats, however it takes 2-3 to kill reanimated drudges.. <br /><br />Keep the one your hunting rooted so if/when charm breaks its easier to deal with just one.. If/when charm breaks try and kite it close enough to the other mob then re-root that way you can sick it back on mob you am killing... <br /><br />I highly recommend grabbing an Aego or all the HP buffs you can because a slowed reanimated drudge and a hasted pissed off vampyre bat that just broke charm are no fun to deal with...<br /><br />I've heard you can charm a reanimated drudge if you find the right one, but I've had no luck.. gotten a couple skeletal drudges' but I've found vampyre bats are better then skeletal drudge... and in<br /><br />Just for my inside pleasure I like to pretend "A reanimated <i>DRUDGE</i>" is really "A reanimated <b><i>DRUID</b></i>"<br /><br /><center><h4>Dobiwon Na`Regen™</h4>57 Defiler<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.htmlq?num=208823" target="_blank"><font color="gold">Mah Crappy Gear</font id="gold"></a></center></span id="msg"></font>
