                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I have also been playing in ME charming stuff...<br />this is what i use and seem to like it<br /><br />spell 1 dooming<br />spell 2 bond<br />spell 3 augmentation<br />spell 4 thrall<br />spell 5 screaming terror<br />spell 6 root<br />spell 7 lich<br />spell 8 feign<br /><br />what i do is look for anything i can charm, prefered pets being reanimated drudge, Xi Xius, Xi Vius... i like the Xi's because they Cheal themselves when low and me when i get low (saves mana on healing self)<br /><br />basically what i do is park the buffed pet (Xi Xius) somewhere with lots of room to run around.  pull the closest mob with darkness and root it near pet.  while the pet is beating on the mob i get another and do the same... usually i have about 4 waiting patiently to die =) all being snared and rooted.  with a cleric pet he keeps his health up and sometimes heals you if you get low and are nearby so you dont have to look for a new pet and rebuff.  when cahrm breaks i use screaming terror to mez the pet and then recharm... mez breaks in about 30 seconds and back to the killing<br /><br />only problem with this is that the Xi pets will cast retribution on you when charm breaks so you have about 5 seconds while its casting to get out of range (unlikely) or mez it<br /><br />i dont really know the rate of exp here as i have been working on levels not AA's.  also i have been having too much fun doing it to pay attention... nothing gets the blood pumping like having snare, root and charm break while your bringing in another mob and having 3 pissed off mobs chase you around till you get things under controll again<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
