                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The reanimated drudges that hit for 149, 151, can be charmed. All above that are too high. Since there are 6 single-spawns of reanimated drudges, one trap and one double-spawn, finding a charmable one just takes time.<br /><br />Not sure if it's all in the mind, but the trap spawns all seem slightly more powerful for their level.<br /><br />Hungry Earth is my root of choice, simply because it does damage as well as holding them down, and is rarely resisted. If after a raid, I have an hour or two of KEI and Ageo left, I can run around in ME and gain an AA happily.<br /><br />Oh, and melee mobs attacking a rooted mob do not affect the duration of the root. Don't know where you got that one from.<br /><br />- Drash Theardark - Aquagnome</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
